        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Profile;

payload.text:
To fix the "column not found" error and get your marketplace fully functional, you need to run a script in your Supabase dashboard.

### Where to update it:

1.  Log in to your [Supabase Dashboard](https://supabase.com/dashboard).
2.  Select your project: **ueeraardwqehsrgfbrii**.
3.  On the left-hand sidebar, click on the **SQL Editor** icon (it looks like a `>_` symbol).
4.  Click **"New query"** (or use the default blank one).
5.  **Paste the SQL code below** into the editor.
6.  Click the **Run** button at the bottom right.

---

### The SQL Script:

This script will safely add the missing columns to your existing table and set up the chat system.

```sql
-- 1. FIX LISTINGS TABLE (Adds missing columns if they aren't there)
create table if not exists public.listings (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null,
  title text not null,
  brand text,
  size text,
  gender text,
  price numeric not null,
  condition text not null,
  category text not null,
  location text not null,
  description text,
  image_url text,
  seller_id uuid not null default auth.uid()
);

-- Specific fix for your error: ensures these columns exist
alter table public.listings add column if not exists gender text;
alter table public.listings add column if not exists size text;

-- 2. SETUP MESSAGING SYSTEM
create table if not exists public.conversations (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null,
  listing_id uuid references public.listings(id) on delete cascade,
  buyer_id uuid not null,
  seller_id uuid not null
);

create table if not exists public.messages (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null,
  conversation_id uuid references public.conversations(id) on delete cascade,
  sender_id uuid not null,
  text text not null
);

-- 3. ENABLE SECURITY (RLS)
alter table public.listings enable row level security;
alter table public.conversations enable row level security;
alter table public.messages enable row level security;

-- 4. PERMISSIONS (Policies)
-- Listings
drop policy if exists "Anyone can view listings" on public.listings;
create policy "Anyone can view listings" on public.listings for select using (true);

drop policy if exists "Users can add items" on public.listings;
create policy "Users can add items" on public.listings for insert with check (auth.uid() = seller_id);

drop policy if exists "Users can delete their items" on public.listings;
create policy "Users can delete their items" on public.listings for delete using (auth.uid() = seller_id);

-- Conversations
drop policy if exists "Users can see their conversations" on public.conversations;
create policy "Users can see their conversations" on public.conversations
  for select using (auth.uid() = buyer_id or auth.uid() = seller_id);

drop policy if exists "Users can start conversations" on public.conversations;
create policy "Users can start conversations" on public.conversations
  for insert with check (auth.uid() = buyer_id);

-- Messages
drop policy if exists "Users can see messages in their conversations" on public.messages;
create policy "Users can see messages in their conversations" on public.messages
  for select using (
    exists (
      select 1 from public.conversations 
      where id = conversation_id and (buyer_id = auth.uid() or seller_id = auth.uid())
    )
  );

drop policy if exists "Users can send messages" on public.messages;
create policy "Users can send messages" on public.messages
  for insert with check (auth.uid() = sender_id);
```

### What to do after running:
Once you see "Success" in the Supabase console, go back to your app. You should now be able to list clothing items with a gender/size selected without getting that error! 

*Note: If you still see the error for 30 seconds, refresh your browser tabŌĆösometimes Supabase needs a moment to update its "schema cache".*

